        boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)

        Determines whether or not the specified Object is equal to this Thing42orNull. The specified Object is equal to this Thing42orNull if it is an instance of Thing42; if its level is the same as this Thing42orNull; and if its key, data, peers, and pool are the same as this Thing42orNull via the equals predicate.
